        <div class="title">
            <h1> Perpetual Motion Machine </h1>
            <p>
                by Bárbara Baron
            </p>
            <p>
                Collage on two MDF panels, metal chain with currency and payphone key, various electronic components. Individual dimensions of 18 x 24 Inches.
            </p>
            <p>
                2022
            </p>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="description">
            <h2>Description</h2>
            <p>
               ‘Perpetual Motion Machine’ is a diptych constructed of images, real-world objects, and circuit-bent electronics. My goal was to experiment with more pictorial representations of themes I’ve been working with while introducing multiple electronic components that work simultaneously.

I’m interested in motion, and I tried to convey that by introducing loops and actions that are triggered by different components within the painting. In this piece, I tried to explore the visual representations of patterns resulting from the passage of time within a living environment. 

            </p>
        </div>

